<topic xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" base="Princeton" id="Sys_Config_ROM_Img_Enable" xml:lang="en-US">
  <title>ROM Image Enable</title>

  <body>
    <p>The ROM Image Enable command is used to
    enable/disable a valid option ROM image. When itâ€™s enabled, the ROM image
    is being loaded and executed when the host system boots. Otherwise, the
    image is ignored when the host system boots.</p>

    <fig id="NVM_Express_Vendor_Specific_Command_ROM__4zht97qqbw">
      <title>NVM Express Vendor Specific Command ROM
      Image Enable Control Flow</title>

      <image href="Graphics/Admin Command Manager/Admin_Rom_Image_Enable.svg" placement="break" width="5.5in"/>
    </fig>

    <table id="_50ht97qqbw">
      <title>NVM Express Vendor Specific Command ROM
      Image Enable Control Flow</title>

      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth=".5in"/>

        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.5in"/>

        <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="4in"/>

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>No.</entry>

            <entry>Message</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">1</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady64</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The command is
            received by one of the Data Managers.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">2</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Data
            Manager forwards the command to the Admin Command Manager for
            processing.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">-</b> </p></entry>

            <entry/>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Manager updates the option ROM configuration in
            superblock.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">3</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">WriteSuperBlkReq</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Manager sends write super block request to Control
            Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">4</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">FlashWrite</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Control
            Manager issues flash write request.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">5</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">FlashOpCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Flash
            Interface responds to flash write request.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">6</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">WriteSuperBlkCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Control
            Manager sends a write superblock completion to Admin
            Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">7</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdate</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Command Manager sends a completion queue update request to the
            Completion Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">8</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdateCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Completion
            Manager replies back to the Admin Command Manager when the
            completion has been successfully sent to the host.</p></entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </body>
</topic>